comments: Finney-Smith (DAL) brushes Murray's (SAS) right arm and marginal contact occurs as Murray starts his drive.
Powell (DAL) makes contact to Murray's (SAS) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Brunson (DAL) brings his off-arm toward Murray's (SAS) side and marginal contact occurs as Brunson releases away.
McDermott (SAS) is moving toward the top of perimeter with his left forearm extended and marginal contact occurs with Brunson's (DAL) front during the drive.
Johnson (SAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Finney-Smith's (DAL) path and absorbs the contact.
Following the release of Johnson's (SAS) shot attempt near the rim, Finney-Smith (DAL) makes contact with Johnson's head that affects his follow through.
McDermott (SAS) hedges the pick and Brunson (DAL) moves through the marginal body contact.
White (SAS) extends his hand into Doncic's (DAL) path and marginal contact occurs to Doncic's front as he drives.

White (SAS) brushes Doncic's (DAL) right arm and marginal contact occurs as he is passing. Murray (SAS) maintains a legal guarding position as incidental contact occurs with Doncic at the end of the drive.
Vassell (SAS) jumps alongside Finney-Smith's (DAL) path and he cleanly blocks the dunk attempt as marginal body contact occurs.
Following the shot attempt, Finney-Smith (DAL) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Vassell (SAS) briefly has his arms around Powell's (DAL) upper half before correcting.
Powell (DAL) makes incidental contact with Vassell's (SAS) back as Vassell retrieves the rebound.
Finney-Smith (DAL) has his hand rested on Murray's (SAS) right hip and marginal contact occurs with Murray's side and lower half during his upward shooting motion.
Johnson (SAS) makes incidental body contact with Powell's (DAL) back as they each attempt to retrieve the rebound.
Vassell (SAS) moves toward Brunson (DAL) as Brunson receives the pass along the sideline and marginal body contact occurs with Brunson's back.
Vassell (SAS) extends his arm into Brunson's (DAL) path and marginal contact occurs with Brunson's front as he drives toward the lane.
Vassell (SAS) legally contests Brunson's (DAL) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Brunson's (DAL) left leg extends forward as he releases the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Vassell's (SAS) lower half.

Hardaway Jr. (DAL) engages with White (SAS) during the inbound and some contact occurs with White's front/arm as he receives the inbound, causing White to momentarily fumble the ball, which he quickly recovers.
White (SAS) is turning away from Brunson (DAL) as they come together along the perimeter and marginal body contact occurs.
Brunson (DAL) makes contact with the part of White's (SAS) hand that is on the ball and dislodges it away from White prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
White (SAS) moves forward into Brunson (DAL) and initiates contact with Brunson's side/arm after he receives the pass.
Ntilikina (DAL) initiates contact across Murray's (SAS) arm as he receives the pass.
McDermott (SAS) and Brunson (DAL) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound after the made free throw.
Johnson (SAS) and Finney-Smith (DAL) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound after the timeout.
McDermott (SAS) commits a take foul on Ntilikina (DAL).
Doncic (DAL) legally contests Walker IV's (SAS) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Murray (SAS) commits a take foul on Brunson (DAL).
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) moves toward the sideline and marginal body contact occurs with Murray (SAS) as he receives the inbound pass.
After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined Brunson's (DAL) free throw attempt does not make contact with the rim.
Murray (SAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Doncic's (DAL) path and gives Doncic a step of distance to avoid the contact, which Murray absorbs.
Johnson (SAS) does not inbound the ball within five seconds.
There is not clear and conclusive video evidence determining if Murray's (SAS) foot lands out of bounds as he receives the pass.
Vassell (SAS) attempts to commit a take foul on Finney-Smith (DAL) and the contact is marginal.
